author: ehillenius
msg: * users can now easily/ elegantly let components contribute header elements like java script and css references
* those references will be filtered for doubles so ppl don't end up with duplication in their pages
* due to the recent refactorings of PackageResourceReference, adding wrong references will fail fast which results in better robustness

author: ehillenius
msg: * More flexible now as it works by commands that can be registered on tag types (tag name)
* img en script tags are now supported as well (and that's a great improvement for header contributions)

* Vary resolving behavior according to tag type in favor of extension. the type of tag is used first, and in the case of actual links, the extension is taken into account; is the extension found then a bookmarkable page link will be created, else a link to a package resource is made
